webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Interior of the Church of Skårdnäs. A lot of older churches carry the complicated building history. Current creation was completed in 1796. The church was painted by Carl Fredrik Beurling in Norrköping. “The coleur should look pearl color with little black” is called, and this Sengustavian color stand is partially preserved. Beurling also delivered the pulpit, which was bestowed by Countess Hedvig Eleonora Falkenberg, born Wachtmeister. The altarpiece is painted in 1802 by the much-used church painter Pehr Hörberg, who reproduced the subject of “Jesus' declaration with Moses and Aaron.” - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFB000558. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021016419874. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
